f=Governance/board/operational/skill/board-skill-routing.md · p=Board's routing map: gate sequence, early-exit rules, handoffs. Sourced skill's Boundaries section. trigger phrases, see `operational/commands/board-commands.md`. · h2:Where Identity Fits=Board Governance's department leader carries active identity `identity/` (currently `principled-gatekeeper-charlie-munger.md`). Identity governs *how* rulings communicated; file governs *which skill runs when*. Identity never overrides sequence any skill's method. · h2:The Gate Sequence=`1. constitution-enforcement     (categorical never-do's) \· VIOLATION → STOP. Review ends; paths: change decision / operator amends constitution. \· 2. strategic-veto               (locked strategy commitments) \· VETO → STOP. Review ends; appeal paths: amend via marcus+operator / re-scope. \· 3. fiduciary-guard              (spend thresholds — only if the decision commits spend)` · h2:The Gate Sequence=decision submitted governance review runs gates order, early exits: Early exits point: unconstitutional decision doesn't get budget review, vetoed one doesn't consume risk workshop. · h2:Handoff Rules=**constitution-enforcement strategic-veto**: rules keep needing exceptions migrate *out* constitution categorical rules stay article form, expiring bets belong locked commitments, tunable numbers fiduciary config. skill flags misplaced rules toward right layer., **fiduciary-guard pre-mortem**: CONDITIONAL resting shaky return estimate routes estimate pre-mortem testing., **pre-mortem risk-assessment-matrix**: pre-mortem generates triages failure scenarios; CRITICAL items enter matrix rows scored gated. routine decisions, matrix alone suffices; major commitments, run pre-mortem first., **risk-assessment-matrix risk register**: scored risks log configured register future Risk department's input., **All skills decision log**: ruling logged (constitution rulings, vetoes appeals, fiduciary recommendations operator overrules, risk rulings). log precedent stream Governance department's precedent agent (Institutional Memory, built) consume. · h2:Cross-Agent Boundaries=**marcus improves, board gates.** decision-critic/venture-priority-matrix sharpen proposal before submission; board rules submitted proposal. Passing marcus's red-team skip any gate., **marcus (with operator) sets what board enforces.** Locked commitments come marcus's strategy process; board never amends them (strategic-veto appeal path routes there). constitution belongs operator alone., **vista's flagged roadmap items** (cut/defer/accelerate) route marcus, board unless resulting decision commits spend above gate touches commitment, which point enters sequence like any decision. · h2:Precedence Request Matches Multiple Skills=full submitted decision runs whole sequence that's default. request naming one check ("just risk-score this") runs skill alone, note gates obviously apply haven't run. See `board-commands.md`. · f=request doesn't fit sequence any single gate, ask what ruling actually sought rather forcing review nobody requested consistent identity's "sit your hands" trait skill's clarify-first guidance.